other_tests.procedure_name: Cimetidine Treatment for Acute Intermittent Porphyria
other_tests.findings: Urinary porphobilinogen (PBG) levels decreased significantly, showing improvement in symptoms after treatment with intravenous cimetidine.
other_tests.changes_over_time: PBG levels fluctuated over time, with measurements showing levels ranging from 75 to 137 /H9262mol/d after initial treatment and continued stability in subsequent follow-ups.
